This paper deals with generative adversarial networks (GANs) for image-to-image translation, specifically on multi-contrast MR images. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses deep learning methods, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses quantitative error measurements, which could fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
